s to send reports, then continues running. So the state hasn't really changed. The pipeline looks healthy with no failures or blockers, and I'm ready to send this as a plain text report.\n\nBut I need to reconsider the instructions more carefully. The task says to send the report to group -5163901258 via Telegram, but I'm supposed to return it as plain text and let it be delivered automatically. The task notes that if external messaging is required, I should note where it should go instead of sending it myself. Looking back at the session history, earlier attempts to send messages to that group through subagents actually did succeed—the group session received messages from the cron job.\n\nComparing the current state to the last stable baseline, the pipeline remains healthy with all four core sessions running normally and no failures detected. Since nothing has changed, I'll just stay silent."},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current session state against stored baseline (last confirmed stable: ~20:29 UTC via session history).\n\n**Critical sessions — baseline vs. now:**\n\n| Session | Baseline (~20:29 UTC) | Current (21:22 UTC) | Δ |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `cron:ed2d0b5d` | ✅ running | ✅ running (~1h51m) | — |\n| `cron:6f3323ef` | ✅ running | ✅ running | — |\n| `cron:e7885813` | ✅ running | ✅ running | — |\n| `telegram:group:-5163901258` | ✅ running (stale ~33m) | ✅ running | — |\n| `main` | ✅ done | ✅ done | — |\n\nAll sessions stable. No failures. No blockers. **Pipeline: HEALTHY.**\n\n**Silent — no state changes detected.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":25035,"output":921,"totalTokens":40329,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":429,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776201778780,"responseId":"062de3348d87860446e7bcb20dd29286","__openclaw":{"id":"c4d24ff9","seq":5}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:main","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","origin":{"provider":"heartbeat"},"displayNa